text.text: Avoid station at all costs. Although the name implies that this is Montpellier it is extremely difficult to get to the named city. Hundreds of people arrive at the same time needing to get a bus shuttle tickets via non functional ticketing machines. Once the bus arrives good luck getting on it (hundreds of people, remember?). The shuttle bus will take you to a central bus station that would eventually get you to the city. Maybe. Taxi? Good luck. Plan to spend hours at the brink of tears contemplating going back to wherever you came from.

text.text:
It's New, so new there is still construction outside, the main waiting hall is spacious with solo seats and table seating, there are three small kiosks, not yet occupied and a Relay outlet that was closed on my visit (outside arrival departure times)

What's here :
Free wifi throughout,
Quiet room,
Children's play room,
Accessible Toilets,
Information Office.

Getting Here
From Airport:
Bus 120 (Herault Transport)

From Montpellier
Bus 120 (Herault Transport)
Departs Place De Europe

Tram + Bus / Walk
Tram Route 1, (direction Odysseum)
To place de France,
(20mins from Saint Roch)

From place de France take Bus Navette Gares, (Station shuttle) 8mins

Or From Place de France walk, it's 1.2km.
The bus must take a scenic route but the walking route is very direct.
As you leave the Tram continue walking in the same direction , with the Aquarium on your right walk to the Car Park, using the walk way / footpath continue out to the road, crossing at the pedestrian crossing you will find yourself at the road to the Station, Footpath all the way.

text.text:
A nice small airport located only 15 minutes drive from the center of Montpellier and very easily accessible. The Airport was not busy and transit through security was quick and efficient.
The staff were polite and smiling and the airport was well organized. It was easy to find the way around.
The airport had a nice Cafe, a reasonably sized duty free shop and children's play area.
It also had a very nice open air terrace near gates 16 and 17. Ideal for relaxing in the fresh air before the flight.
Overall a very pleasant airport to travel through.

editorialSummary.text: Scandinavian chain selling ready-to-assemble furniture, plus textiles, lighting & home decor.

text.text:
Wanted to visit IKEA, but we didn't think that we could park as we have a motorhome. However if you drive past the car entrance and take the first exit off the roundabout you can park up in the deliveries area. There is a barrier and you need to press the button to ask for entry. Then you just need to follow the signage to the store entrance.
We enjoyed our visit and our lunch, even though there was a huge queue in the restaurant. Fish and chips were not brilliant, but the salmon, desserts and the hot chocolate were all good.

text.text: Bought a bed base and mattress online. I booked and paid for a specific day of delivery. Pantoja the delivery company called and stated due to driver shortage they could not deliver but IKEA would call me to rebook. IKEA never called. When I called them they booked it for a Saturday delivery. On the day of delivery after several hours of waiting I notice the online tracking shows the delivery has been cancelled. So I have paid money for a bed which I now cannot cancel but 3 weeks later I still don't have.

editorialSummary.text: Zoo with more than 1100 animals & 128 species, including lions, plus a lush Amazonian greenhouse.

text.text:
Not sure what to expect after the reviews, but the park suprised me. I would recommend going there.
First of all, it has free parking and entrance!
The areas for the animals are large (which is a good thing) so sometimes you need to search for them. The park is 50/50 animals and a walk area. But all well maintained.
Bring drinks/water for sure, and some snacks/food. Almost everywhere you can walk in the shade, and the distance you can decide yourself following different routes.

editorialSummary.text: Large, contemporary aquarium with hands-on, high-tech exhibits, including 3D ocean simulator rides.

text.text:
Nice place to enjoy with kids independent of the day. They got a lot of different kind of aquariums with penguins, sharks, etc. a lot of additional educational stuff as well. The last 10% of the visit targets the universe - didn't get that break in the narrative. But the large planetarium-like movie theatre with the songs and animations was very entertaining!

You will likely not spend more than 2hrs - the parking is free for 2:15 hrs and the Entrance fee raised to 19,50€ recently, kids free up to 3 yrs. We were here off season, at 10 am they opened and it was a short line but quickly filled up.

The last 10% of the visit targets the universe - didn't get that break in the narrative. But the large planetarium-like movie theatre with the songs and animations was very entertaining!

You will likely not spend more than 2hrs - the parking is free for 2:15 hrs and the Entrance fee raised to 19,50€ recently, kids free up to 3 yrs. We were here off season, at 10 am they opened and it was a short line but quickly filled up.

text.text: A fantastic aquarium that had my 11-year-old literally in awe at the displays and variety on offer. He was running from place to place not giving us a chance to catch up! It’s such a cool interactive experience for him and we loved our time here.

text.text: Loved this aquarium. Make sure you book tickets online the day before, you can bypass the bug queue that way. And they last months too! Lots to see and nice and cool inside. Staff speak different languages, a nice touch for those of us that need respite from taxing our little brains. We were surprised at how cheap refreshments were in the cafe! Lovely. Definitely recommend for all ages.

text.text:
A one of a kind discovery.
This place is very hard to miss. You’re gonna love coming here and enjoying yourself with all varieties of food with different taste to share with your friends and drinks to have with different vibes of music in each and every corner.
You can change places too as there are some clubs upstairs though they seemed a little too much for my taste as it seemed like they only welcomed very posh people in.

But apart from that you have lots of places to go and look around. Though you’ll have to be careful about finding a parking as it can get super crowded on weekends and Friday nights.

I highly recommend to check this place out !

text.text: Come for the view! Enjoy your walk and see this park; you can overlook the aqueduct at the pavilion at its eastern end. Went there early afternoon and easily found a place to sit and relax a bit. It’s a traditional park in France, don’t expect flowers but more pavement and a good view across statue towards church and city.
